<p>How can I enable clustering so instead of showing markers it is clustered? For example: <a href="https://www.police.uk/metropolitan/00BK17N/crime/" rel="nofollow">https://www.police.uk/metropolitan/00BK17N/crime/</a></p>  <p>users_controller</p>  <pre><code>class UsersController &lt; ApplicationController   def index     @users = User.all     @hash = Gmaps4rails.build_markers(@users) do |user, marker|       marker.lat user.latitude       marker.lng user.longitude       marker.infowindow user.description     end   end end </code></pre>  <p>index.html.erb</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div id="map-container"&gt;   &lt;div id="map-canvas"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;script&gt; $(document).ready(function(){   handler = Gmaps.build('Google');   handler.buildMap({ provider: {}, internal: {id: 'map-canvas'}}, function(){     markers = handler.addMarkers(&lt;%=raw @hash.to_json %&gt;)     handler.bounds.extendWith(markers);     handler.fitMapToBounds(markers);     if(navigator.geolocation)       navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition;   }); }); &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Appreciate your help guys</p>